From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 23:14:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 41/64] web-app: sender-baked link previews with a composer
 ghost UI
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

When the draft contains a URL and no image is attached, the composer shows a
quiet, dismissible ghost offering to add a link preview. Accepting fetches the
link's OpenGraph metadata, renders a preview card into a PNG on the sender's
device, and attaches it as the message image; the link text stays in the body.

Because the result is an ordinary text + image message, the recipient's client
never contacts the link (no IP/metadata leak, keeps E2EE intact) and every
client renders it as-is — nothing to implement on the receive side. This is a
UI prototype: the baked-image approach is a compromise to validate the composer
UX now; the eventual design moves generation into core with the preview carried
as structured message metadata, and this card becomes a renderer over it.

New packages/frontend/src/components/composer/linkPreview/ module wired into
Composer.tsx:
- detectUrl: first previewable http(s) URL in the draft (debounced).
- openGraph: preview metadata types + the compact-vs-hero layout heuristic.
- renderCard: canvas → PNG card (opaque light surface so it reads on any
  recipient theme; measured layout; shrink-to-fit ≤ 0.6 MB; play glyph for video).
- generate: fetch via the bridge's unfurl endpoint (webapp-only — the browser
  fetch is CORS-bound and near-useless direct, so there is no direct tier; the
  bridge fetches server-side and returns metadata + image as JSON). Derives the
  endpoint from the configured bridge URL (?proxy=, ws→http); unreachable →
  UnfurlUnavailableError.
- useLinkPreview: the ghost state machine. Gates on a 'user has their own file'
  signal (mirrored in a ref so our own attach isn't mistaken for a user file);
  dismissal is per-message (forgotten once the composer has no URL); a
  generation timeout; abort-token invalidation on URL change.
- LinkPreviewGhost: idle ghost → loading bar → ready chip (the baked card shown
  big with a labeled ⤢ Bigger / ⤡ Smaller size toggle and remove) → an
  'unavailable' hint when the unfurl endpoint can't be reached.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
